  "texts": [
    "However, the advent of larger language models has opened up new avenues for analyzing data with limited labeled examples.",
    "This thesis explores the efficacy of techniques like zero-shot and few-shot learning, along with the use of adapters for continuous training, in both small and large language models.",
    "The central hypothesis of this research is that few-shot prompt engineering offers a costeffective and efficient solution for sentiment analysis in the context of commodity markets.",
    "To test this hypothesis, the study investigates the performance of various models, including those trained on economic domain-specific datasets build of abstracts and those trained with added trained adapters.",
    "The findings of this research are designed to contribute to the development of more accurate and efficient tools for economic analysis and forecasting.It is important to acknowledge the environmental costs associated with training large language models."
  ],
